
Brandnew from the CeBIT 1993 - Commodore presents the A4000T , A4000/030 and
A4091

On this years CeBIT, world's biggest computer and communication fair, held
in  Hannover, Germany, Commodore presents the new high-end machine
Commodore Amiga 4000 T. 
This machine has the same ablilities as it's small brother, the A4000.
But it contains the A4091 SCSI-2 adaptor. (onboard ?)

The long-awaited A4000/030 completes the AA machines in the mid-range.
This machine has all the features as the A4000, but has the MC68EC030
(68030 without MMU) as CPU.

Also long-awaited is the A4091, a full blown SCSI-2 host adaptor for
Zorro-III Slots. This adaptor makes it possible to transfer at max.
20MB synchronous. Yet a hard drive which is capable to transfer this
has to be found... No further specs can be given right now.

-------------------------
