For the Slots: (A4000T)
Seems that 5 Slots for Amiga and 4 Slots for ISA are in fact not more than
total 7 Slots, as 2 of the ISA Slots are blocked by 2 Amiga Slots.

_NO_ mentionings about a SECOND Video-Slot for the A4000T.

The tower-case of the A4000T looks like one of the Commodore PC-486-tower-
cases. It has a door which hides the drives. All connectors on the rear
side. The SCSI-2 external connector is compatible to the SCSI-2 connector
of Sun and DEC. 

Note: I can only bring you the specs noted in a broshure given to
      me by Commodore. You should ask your local dealer for more
      information.

